nd. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":98,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":109,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Augusta Mattern was born in 1460, in Derby, Derbyshire, England as the daughter of CARL Boris Mattern. She married Sir John Boris in 1480, in Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England."},"et":{"1460–":"1460–Surnud","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1455–Male":"1455–Surnud","1485–1585":"1485–1585","1440–Male":"1440–Surnud","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1455":"1455","1585":"1585","1485":"1485","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1549":"1549","Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England","Chesterfield, , Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England","chesterfield, derbyshire, england":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England","Derby, Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"1460–":"1460–Kuollut","1460–Female":"1460–Kuollut","1455–Male":"1455–Kuollut","1485–1585":"1485–1585","1440–Male":"1440–Kuollut","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1455":"1455","1585":"1585","1485":"1485","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1549":"1549","Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England":"Chesterfield, Derbyshire, Englan